 how scientists uncover evolutionary history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAdaptation (Biology). 0aEvolution (Biology). 0aEvolution. 0aExtremities (Anatomy)xEvolution. 0aLungsxEvolution. 0aVertebratesxEvolution. 0aVertebrates, Fossil. 7aSCIENCE / Paleontology.2bisacsh  aacanthostega.  aacquired limbs.  aactinopterygians.  aadaptation.  acharacter evolution.  adinosaurs.  aevolution.  aevolutionary history.  aevolutionary processes.  aevolutionary science.  aextant species.  aextant vertebrates.  aextinct animals.  afinned vertebrates.  afossils.  ageology.  alife on earth.  alife sciences.  alimbs.  amolecular dating.  anonfiction.  apaleontological dating.  apaleontology.  aphylogeny.  apopular science.  ascience.  atetrapods.  avertebrate animals.  avertebrates.  azoology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026647640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094798640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947986/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY